  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The device is intended for continuous in vivo deployment across extended surgical and post-operative perfusion periods lasting up to 72 hours, operating in clinical environments subject to electrical noise, vibration from adjacent surgical equipment, and potential wear-induced degradation of the pump motor and bearing assemblies over repeated sterilization and re-use cycles.",
